# .gcloudignore — controls the build context uploaded by `gcloud builds submit`.
#
# Authored job-0240-infra-20260610 for the MODFLOW + python-sandbox Cloud Build
# submits. The build context is the repo root (`.`) because both Dockerfiles use
# repo-root-relative COPYs (services/workers/modflow/, infra/python-sandbox/).
#
# Without this file gcloud falls back to .gitignore semantics but STILL uploads
# untracked-not-ignored files — which here is ~1 GB of mf6 6.5.0 zips + extracted
# binaries left in reports/inflight/**/verify/ by prior smoke runs (job-0220 /
# job-0221). Those are irrelevant to the Docker build (the image curls mf6 itself)
# and would bloat the upload. We keep the context to the source the Dockerfiles
# actually COPY plus what they need at build time.
#
# Strategy: ignore the known-heavy / build-irrelevant trees, then re-include the
# two source dirs the Dockerfiles COPY from so they are never accidentally
# excluded by a broad pattern.

# Version control + tooling
.git/
.gitignore

# Heavy / build-irrelevant trees (none are COPY'd by either Dockerfile)
reports/
web/
docs/
agents/
tests/
evidence/
styles/
packages/

# Python / Node / Terraform build detritus
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.venv/
**/.venv*/
**/node_modules/
**/.terraform/
**/dist/
**/build/

# Re-include the two source trees the Dockerfiles COPY (repo-root relative):
#   MODFLOW Dockerfile:  COPY services/workers/modflow/ ...
#   sandbox  Dockerfile: COPY infra/python-sandbox/executor.py ...
!services/
!services/workers/
!services/workers/modflow/
!services/workers/modflow/**
!infra/
!infra/python-sandbox/
!infra/python-sandbox/**
!infra/modflow/
!infra/modflow/**

# Even within the re-included trees, drop caches/zips
services/workers/modflow/__pycache__/
infra/python-sandbox/__pycache__/
